  "texts": [
    "However, when we replaced the session ID with the correct one, all of these messages were accepted by the server.For our approach, we developed two methods to improve the LLM's capability of incorporating correct session IDs when provided with additional context information.",
    "We first included the server's responses in the prompt and then requested the LLM to generate the same types of messages.",
    "At this time, the generated client requests were directly accepted by the the PLAY state (d) In the RECORD state State transition No transition Inappropriate 81% 81% 17% 2% 74% 16% 10% 69% 30% 1% 89% 10% 1% Fig. 5.",
    "The next types of client requests generated by the LLM in each state.",
    "The types in gray induce state transitions, the ones in orange appear in the suitable state but do not trigger state transitions, and the ones in blue appear in the inappropriate states."
